Title: CEO & Founder
Description: Ashford Communities was founded by Ash Kumar in 1998, shortly after moving from Canada with his family. Mr. Kumar began buying apartment properties while still a student at the University of Regina in Canada. He grew his business by analyzing each property, buying under market value and improving the properties to increase resident occupancies. Throughout his acquisitions, Mr. Kumar has taken great pride in giving back to the community as he felt there should be a way in which a business could prosper even more by providing residents with a positive experience within their community. He was right; rebranding HK Capital to Ashford Communities and establishing community building as the company's business model resulted in 70% resident retention (double industry average). His strategy focuses on implementing programs, such as English classes or health camps, to promote a sense of brotherhood among residents, ultimately resulting in recurrent lease renewals despite rent increases. Ashford Communities has expanded its portfolio to 13 complexes reflecting a growth of 350% over the last four years and is one of the main sponsors of TotoAid, the organization founded alongside his wife, which provides education for children in Tanzania from elementary all the way thru college. Despite achieving rapid business success, Mr. Kumar did not allow it to impede him from expanding his knowledge further. He is currently focused on his academic growth and has enrolled inthe Harvard OPM Class of 2015 and EMP EO Class of 2017.  He is also a founding member of Houston’s CEO Group Vistage (highest growth 2008, 2014, 2015, 2016) and a founding member of EO Houston.

Title: President
Description:
LINKED IN PROFILE:

Judy Camarena seamlessly bridges the gap between tradition and transformation.

In less than a decade, Camarena has taken Arandas Franchises from a string of family-run franchises struggling to find a unified identity to a thriving, recognizable brand expanding into a growing number of markets with an increasingly diversified portfolio.

Before the age of 30, Camarena took her father’s dream – a traditional Mexican-style taqueria – and developed it into what now comprises nearly 30 Taquerias Arandas branch locations in Houston and Dallas, five Arandas Bakeries, two Ostioneria Arandas seafood restaurants and a Trailita Arandas mobile unit.

Under Camarena’s innovative leadership – which has spawned a full breakfast menu, new taco menus, full-service bars and specifically-tailored menu options – Taquerias Arandas is gaining a loyal and more diverse following as the company enters new communities, bringing approachable, authentic Mexican food to people who otherwise might not have tried it.

Camarena isn’t afraid to take chances and has helped Taquerias Arandas flourish in an economy where two-thirds of second-generation family businesses fail. Under her watch, Taquerias Arandas sales have increased 52 percent since 2003 and total franchise sales have increased to more than $60 million.

“I respect my family legacy, as well as the traditions and responsibilities that come with that,” Camarena said. “But I think it’s equally important to look to the future to make sure that we keep moving forward as a company.”

Camarena’s foresight and dynamic leadership have earned her multiple awards and accolades, including LATINA Style magazine’s Entrepreneur of the Year award for Houston and the 2006 Entrepreneurial Star Award for “Outstanding Accomplishments & Blazing the Trail on Behalf of Women & Minority Entrepreneurs.” She has also been a speaker at the University of Houston’s Friends of Women’s Studies “Table Talk.”

Title: Partner
Description: I help waste treatment system operators improve their biological process treatment efficiency by evaluating the wastes being treated, existing equipment, operations, and effluent treatment targets. Recent projects include:     •	Application of advanced molecular genetic testing (Environmental Genomics) to environmental         samples     •	Evaluation of new influent streams for impact on biomass      •	Installation of industrial biological pre-treatment programs     •	Biological nutrient removal (both ammonia & phosphate)     •	Indentifiation of cost-control strategies in waste treatment     •	Development of custom bioaugmentation cultures for bioremediation projectsWHO I WORK WITHI work with engineers, wastewater professionals, and microbiologists.  With the background in biological waste treatment and microbial ecology, I have also worked with animal feeding operations, aquaculture, and bioremediation companies to provide customized microbial/enzyme products.WHY IT WORKSBy focusing on biological waste treatment, I offer a different perspective than traditional chemical and equipment companies. Often biological issues are masked by chemical addition, holding back flow, or capital expenditures. Removing existing biological unit bottlenecks offers more efficient and lower waste treatment costs.HOW I DO ITI look for opportunities to enhance biological treatment performance. By combining my experience, the latest research, and a network of environmental professionals, I deliver innovation and a full spectrum of options to my customers.WHAT MAKES ME DIFFERENTI have worked with a wide range of systems, influents, and unique waste challenges. Title: RESTAURANT CEO
Description: Renowned restaurateur, Jim Mazany, has been a crucial part of the success stories of many restaurant and hospitality brands. His career as an industry leader began in 1990 working for Carlson Restaurants Worldwide as the Senior Director of Operations for over 30 restaurants in $83M market. Following his success in this position, Jim moved into the position of Chief Operating Officer for the Apple Gold Group. Managing the operation of over 130 Applebee's and Johnny Carino's, Jim was able to turn this franchise group around and position it to purchase another Applebee's group in just two short years. In 2007, Jim was hired on to Ignite Restaurant Group as Chief Operations Officer. Overseeing over 135 restaurants, Jim Mazany turned Ignite and Joe's Crab Shack into an industry success story resulting in his promotion to President and the company going public. After developing a variety of new management and leadership models and concepts, Jim took his expertise to the founding of a Strategic Restaurant Solutions a national full-service consulting group designed to provide innovative hospitality solutions for mid-to-large sized companies. Today, Jim Mazany is currently acting CEO of Fatz Southern Kitchen and has revitalized the beloved Southern brand. Fatz Southern Kitchen is now on track to be added to Jim's ever-growing list of restaurant turnarounds. Through 30+ years of experience, Jim Mazany has become an expert restaurateur and is uniquely skilled in assessing a brand's strengths and weaknesses and shaping it for a future of success."VISIONARY RESULTS DRIVEN RESTAURANT EXECUTIVEAvailable for consulting engagements as well as full-time opportunities, please contact me directly at jmazany@srsolutions.com.
